  description: 'In 1090, a man disguised as a schoolteacher walked into an impregnable mountain fortress and took it without a single drop of blood. For the next 166 years, his followers would terrify sultans, caliphs, and Crusader kings with a weapon no army could counter: a single man with a dagger, willing to die. This is the true story of the Assassins \u2014 and the myths that made them immortal.',
